    <abstract id="aspace_9a1b7b25201ffa6a57124fdf814aa9ae">Located in Belmont, N.C.  Founded in 1876 as St. Mary's College for men by the Benedictine Monks of St. Vincent's Archabbey, Latrobe, PA.  Chartered by North Carolina in 1886.  In 1913 name changed to Belmont Abbey College.  In 1928 it was reorganized as a junior college until 1952 when it became a senior college again.</abstract>
